   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The following is a list of steps for migrating a Salesforce org that is currently using CIG package and does not yet have the Power Composer Package installed.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">To begin the migration process and install the Composer Package, you must first uninstall the CIG package. Before uninstalling, it is important that you collect and store all current Power Solutions, Power Queries, and Power Templates on your local desktop. These will have to be recreated and modified to be used in the newly installed Composer Package. It is also necessary to collect and store all users that are assigned permission sets associated with the CIG packages, as these permissions sets will also have to be removed from the users for a successful uninstall. They will need to be reassigned to those users once the Composer Package is successfully installed.</p>
